    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile cut your <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped meat-free chick'n </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways and scrape out the <strong>inner seeds </strong>using a teaspoon and discard</p><p>Slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> <strong>halves </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>remaining natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt</strong> and <strong>mayo</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Zest your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Peel and finely grate (or chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(don't like raw garlic? Go easy!), <strong>lime</strong> <strong>zest</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to the yoghurt \u2013 this is your <strong>lime & garlic yoghurt</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated meat-free chick'n</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly browned \u2013 this is your <strong>tandoori meat-free chick'n</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the meat-free chick'n is browning, pick your <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Chop the <strong>mint</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooled rice</strong>, <strong>black sesame seeds</strong>,<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>cucumber</strong>, <strong>shredded red cabbage </strong>and most of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and <strong>mint </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) to a large bowl</p><p>Squeeze the juice of the <strong>lime[s]</strong> into the bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> rice salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-tandoori-meat-free-chick-n-with-brown-rice-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> tandoori meat-free chick'n</strong> over the <strong>rice salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>lime & garlic yoghurt</strong> all over and garnish with the<strong> remaining chopped mint & coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
